"{\"uid\": \"citizen.co.za-news-news-world-paris-2024-olympic-games-flame-lit-in-ancient-olympia\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Home\\u00bbNews\\u00bbWorld  ByAgence France Presse  5 minute read  16 April 2024  12:38 pm  Greek actress Mary Mina, playing the role of the High Priestess, lights the torch during the flame lighting ceremony for the Paris 2024 Olympics Games at the ancient temple of Hera on the Olympia archeological site, birthplace of the ancient Olympics in southern Greece, on April 16, 2024.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 370, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 81, \"end\": 86, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9999852280029377, \"rank\": 1.4729800540175895e-05, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 95, \"end\": 99, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_II_of_England\", \"score\": 0.9935257692008671, \"rank\": 0.006209786842526448, \"text\": \"Mary\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_II_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_II_of_England\"}, {\"begin\": 257, \"end\": 261, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hera\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.529467183413507e-18, \"text\": \"Hera\", \"types\": [\"Q24229398\", \"Q178885\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hera\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hera\"}, {\"begin\": 269, \"end\": 276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\", \"score\": 0.999999999958618, \"rank\": 4.126466487362202e-11, \"text\": \"Olympia\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\"}, {\"begin\": 344, \"end\": 350, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9999999999545253, \"rank\": 4.53408528056193e-11, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Photo: AFP  The sacred flame for the Paris 2024 Olympic Games was lit Tuesday in Olympia, Greece, the birthplace of the ancient Games, in a ceremony inspired by antiquity and marked by messages of hope amid multiple global crises.\", \"from\": 371, \"to\": 601, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 452, \"end\": 467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia,_Greece\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Olympia, Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia,_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia,_Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 452, \"end\": 467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia,_Greece\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Olympia, Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia,_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia,_Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In ancient times, the Olympic Games brought together the Greek city states, even - and in particular - during times of war and conflict,\\\" said International Olympic Committee President Thomas Bach.\", \"from\": 603, \"to\": 801, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 661, \"end\": 666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9999852280029377, \"rank\": 1.4729800540175895e-05, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 747, \"end\": 778, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 789, \"end\": 800, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Today, the Olympic Games are the only event that brings the entire world together in peaceful competition.\", \"from\": 803, \"to\": 910, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Then as now, the Olympic athletes are sending this powerful message: yes, it is possible to compete fiercely against each other and at the same time live peacefully together under one roof,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 911, \"to\": 1110, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Owing to cloudy weather, Greek actresses in the role of ancient priestesses used a flame lit in a rehearsal Monday in the 2,600-year-old Temple of Hera, near the stadium where the Olympics were born in 776 BC.\", \"from\": 1112, \"to\": 1321, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1137, \"end\": 1142, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9999852280029377, \"rank\": 1.4729800540175895e-05, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 1318, \"end\": 1320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anno_Domini\", \"score\": 0.9699953334164073, \"rank\": 0.030920521451565562, \"text\": \"BC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anno_Domini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anno_Domini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Carrying the flame in a pot, Greek actress Mary Mina lit the torch for the first bearer, 2020 Olympic rowing champion Stefanos Ntouskos.\", \"from\": 1323, \"to\": 1459, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1352, \"end\": 1357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9999852280029377, \"rank\": 1.4729800540175895e-05, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 1366, \"end\": 1370, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_II_of_England\", \"score\": 0.9935257692008671, \"rank\": 0.006209786842526448, \"text\": \"Mary\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_II_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_II_of_England\"}, {\"begin\": 1441, \"end\": 1458, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefanos_Ntouskos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stefanos Ntouskos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefanos_Ntouskos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefanos_Ntouskos\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Retired French swimmer Laure Manaudou, who won her first gold medal at the 2004 Athens Olympics, followed as France's first torchbearer in Olympia.\", \"from\": 1461, \"to\": 1608, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1469, \"end\": 1475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9968493459090574, \"rank\": 0.003152567592297135, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1484, \"end\": 1498, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laure_Manaudou\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laure Manaudou\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laure_Manaudou\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laure_Manaudou\"}, {\"begin\": 1570, \"end\": 1576, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999989522621, \"rank\": 8.864368021725943e-10, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1600, \"end\": 1607, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\", \"score\": 0.999999999958618, \"rank\": 4.126466487362202e-11, \"text\": \"Olympia\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Officials on Tuesday stressed that the Paris Games will set new milestones, following the legacy of the other two prior Olympics held in the French capital.\", \"from\": 1610, \"to\": 1766, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1751, \"end\": 1757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9968493459090574, \"rank\": 0.003152567592297135, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Olympic Flame will shine over the first Olympic Games inspired by our Olympic Agenda reforms from start to finish,\\\" Bach said.\", \"from\": 1768, \"to\": 1899, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1889, \"end\": 1893, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2442943885468466e-14, \"text\": \"Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"These Olympic Games will be younger, more inclusive, more urban, more sustainable.\", \"from\": 1901, \"to\": 1984, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These will be the very first Olympic Games with full gender parity, because the IOC allocated exactly 50 percent of the places to female and male athletes,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1985, \"to\": 2150, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2065, \"end\": 2068, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.724904954162614e-42, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris Olympics chief organiser Tony Estanguet noted that women took part for the first time in the Paris 1900 Games, while the first Olympic Village was created for the Paris 2024 Games.\", \"from\": 2152, \"to\": 2338, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2152, \"end\": 2166, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2183, \"end\": 2197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}, {\"begin\": 2285, \"end\": 2300, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4903475741958941e-25, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the first time since the Covid-19 pandemic imposed toned-down events for the 2020 Tokyo Olympics and 2022 Beijing Winter Games, the ceremony was back with full regalia and scores of spectators.\", \"from\": 2340, \"to\": 2537, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Greek President Katerina Sakellaropoulou, French sports minister Amelie Oudea-Castera and Paris Mayor Anne Hidalgo were present at the ceremony.\", \"from\": 2539, \"to\": 2683, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2539, \"end\": 2554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_Greece\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Greek President\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 2555, \"end\": 2579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katerina_Sakellaropoulou\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katerina Sakellaropoulou\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katerina_Sakellaropoulou\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katerina_Sakellaropoulou\"}, {\"begin\": 2581, \"end\": 2587, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9968493459090574, \"rank\": 0.003152567592297135, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2629, \"end\": 2640, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Mayor\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2641, \"end\": 2653, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"American mezzo soprano Joyce DiDonato delivered the Olympic anthem.\", \"from\": 2685, \"to\": 2752, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2685, \"end\": 2693, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999765751428357, \"rank\": 2.342539561548067e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2708, \"end\": 2722, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joyce_DiDonato\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Joyce DiDonato\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joyce_DiDonato\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joyce_DiDonato\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The torch harks back to the ancient Olympics when a sacred flame burned throughout the Games.\", \"from\": 2754, \"to\": 2847, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The tradition was revived in 1936 for the Berlin Games.\", \"from\": 2848, \"to\": 2903, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"During the 11-day relay on Greek soil, some 600 torchbearers will carry the flame over a distance of 5,000 kilometres (3,100 miles) through 41 municipalities.\", \"from\": 2905, \"to\": 3063, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2932, \"end\": 2937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9999852280029377, \"rank\": 1.4729800540175895e-05, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ALSO READ:With another win in the bag, Gerda Steyn targets Olympic marathon  The Olympic flame will be handed over to Paris 2024 organisers in a ceremony at the all-marble Panathenaic Stadium, site of the first modern Olympic Games of 1896, on April 26.\", \"from\": 3065, \"to\": 3318, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3104, \"end\": 3115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerda_Steyn\", \"score\": 0.9999998978501078, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gerda Steyn\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerda_Steyn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerda_Steyn\"}, {\"begin\": 3146, \"end\": 3159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6661570423054076e-40, \"text\": \"Olympic flame\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\"}, {\"begin\": 3183, \"end\": 3193, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2642780404376316e-34, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nana Mouskouri, the 89-year-old Greek singer with a worldwide following, has been invited to perform at the ceremony.\", \"from\": 3320, \"to\": 3437, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3320, \"end\": 3324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akan_chieftaincy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.394848436392971e-21, \"text\": \"Nana\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akan_chieftaincy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akan_chieftaincy\"}, {\"begin\": 3352, \"end\": 3357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9999852280029377, \"rank\": 1.4729800540175895e-05, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On April 27, the flame will begin its journey to France on board the 19th-century three-masted barque Belem, which was launched just weeks after the Athens 1896 Games.\", \"from\": 3439, \"to\": 3606, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3488, \"end\": 3494, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999989522621, \"rank\": 8.864368021725943e-10, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3541, \"end\": 3546, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bel\\u00e9m\", \"score\": 0.9903282791598326, \"rank\": 0.00799898425596817, \"text\": \"Belem\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bel\\u00e9m\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bel\\u00e9m\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A French historical monument, the Belem carried out trade journeys to Brazil, Guyana and the Caribbean for nearly two decades.\", \"from\": 3608, \"to\": 3734, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3610, \"end\": 3636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monument_historique\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French historical monument\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monument_historique\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monument_historique\"}, {\"begin\": 3642, \"end\": 3647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bel\\u00e9m\", \"score\": 0.9903282791598326, \"rank\": 0.00799898425596817, \"text\": \"Belem\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bel\\u00e9m\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bel\\u00e9m\"}, {\"begin\": 3678, \"end\": 3684, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\", \"score\": 0.999999986337116, \"rank\": 1.1350180191053721e-08, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\"}, {\"begin\": 3686, \"end\": 3692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guyana\", \"score\": 0.9999999995761755, \"rank\": 4.234630732629178e-10, \"text\": \"Guyana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guyana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guyana\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France's last surviving three-mast steel-hulled boat, it is expected to arrive in Marseille on May 8.\", \"from\": 3736, \"to\": 3837, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3818, \"end\": 3827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.975850467789705e-15, \"text\": \"Marseille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ten thousand torchbearers will then carry the flame across 64 French territories.\", \"from\": 3839, \"to\": 3920, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3901, \"end\": 3907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9968493459090574, \"rank\": 0.003152567592297135, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will travel through 400 towns and dozens of tourist attractions during its 12,000-kilometre (7,500-mile) journey through mainland France and overseas French territories in the Caribbean, Indian Ocean and Pacific.\", \"from\": 3922, \"to\": 4137, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4055, \"end\": 4061, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999989522621, \"rank\": 8.864368021725943e-10, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 4075, \"end\": 4081, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9968493459090574, \"rank\": 0.003152567592297135, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On July 26 it will form the centrepiece of the Paris Olympics opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 4139, \"to\": 4218, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The ceremony is planned to be held on the river Seine, the first time it has not been held in the Games' main stadium.\", \"from\": 4220, \"to\": 4338, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, French President Emmanuel Macron on Monday said it could be moved to the national stadium in the event of a security threat.\", \"from\": 4340, \"to\": 4473, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4349, \"end\": 4365, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French President\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/re